# Design Contract

This contract applies to `Pathogen::*` components, Lookbook previews, and host application usage. Feature-level UI specs should cite this contract, follow it by default, and document local exceptions with a short rationale.

## Ownership

- `Pathogen::*` components are the shared cross-project design-system surface.
- New reusable UI should be considered for Pathogen before host-local components.
- Existing host components should conform to Pathogen tokens and accessibility rules while in use.
- Lookbook previews must demonstrate the same product environment host apps should build.

## Philosophical Baseline

**Form follows workflow.** Every visual decision should clarify task structure, state, hierarchy, or navigation. If a choice does not serve the workflow, remove it.

**Less, but better.** Prefer one confident primary action, restrained type weights, flat surfaces, and small purposeful colour fields over expressive composition.

**Inevitability over novelty.** Controls should feel resolved — as if no alternative layout would be more rational for the task. Avoid decorative gradients, hero cards, oversized radius, and marketing-page rhythm in product surfaces.

**Care in the invisible.** Focus rings, keyboard order, ARIA names, forced-colours behaviour, and disabled semantics are part of the design — not implementation details.

## Atomic Hierarchy

Pathogen composes UI from a small set of repeatable atoms. Use the same atom everywhere it applies; do not invent parallel styling.

### 1. Intent

Before choosing classes, name what the element does in the workflow: primary action, secondary dismiss, status, navigation, metadata, destructive confirm, etc. Intent drives tone, emphasis, colour role, and placement.

### 2. Colour roles

Consume semantic roles (`--pvc-color-*`), not raw palette stops (`primary-600`, `slate-200`) in shared components.

| Role family | Use for |
|-------------|---------|
| Surface / muted / raised | Backgrounds and layering |
| Border / border-strong | Edges, dividers, table rules |
| Text / text-muted | Body copy and secondary copy |
| Accent / accent-strong / accent-solid | Brand actions, links, selection |
| Danger / success / warning | Status only |
| Focus | Keyboard focus rings |

Host apps map accent through `--color-primary-*`. Components must not hard-code host brand colours.

**Migration note:** `Pathogen::Button` and `Pathogen::CopyableValue` use semantic roles today. Typography, Link, Tabs, Form, and Tooltip still use `neutral-*` / `primary-*` utilities in places — new and touched code should migrate toward `--pvc-color-*`.

### 3. Typography atoms

| Atom | Token / class | Use for |
|------|---------------|---------|
| Meta | `--type-meta` (12px) / `text-xs` | Hints, timestamps, grid metadata |
| Control | `--type-control` (14px) / `text-sm` | Labels, buttons, dense UI, helper text |
| Body | `--type-body` (16px) / `text-base` | Paragraph copy, form descriptions |
| Section | `--type-section` (20px) / `text-xl` | Section headings inside a page |
| Page | `--type-page` (31px) / `text-3xl`+ | Page-owned headings via `Pathogen::Typography::Heading` |

Rules:

- Default product rhythm is **14px and 16px**. Larger sizes are for hierarchy, not decoration.
- Labels that identify a setting, row, or control: `text-sm font-semibold` (or `--type-control` + semibold).
- Muted copy uses `--pvc-color-text-muted` or the typography `muted` variant.
- Weights stay restrained: normal body, semibold labels/headings. Avoid extrabold except top-level page headings.
- Page headings are component-owned. Host pages must not override size or weight on shared heading components.
- `Pathogen::Typography::Eyebrow` is the only routine uppercase tracked label; do not add display typography elsewhere.

Prefer `text-[length:var(--type-*)]` in new component code so the token scale stays authoritative. Tailwind `text-sm` / `text-base` remain acceptable where they match the token values exactly.

### 4. Spacing atoms

Base unit: **4px** (Tailwind default). Use the scale consistently:

| Step | Class | Typical use |
|------|-------|-------------|
| 4px | `gap-1`, `p-1`, `space-y-1` | Tight inline groups, icon padding |
| 8px | `gap-2`, `p-2`, `space-y-2` | Control internals, compact stacks |
| 16px | `gap-4`, `p-4`, `space-y-4` | Form fields, fieldsets, card padding |
| 24px | `gap-6`, `space-y-6` | Section separation |
| 32px | `gap-8` | Major regions |

Align labels, controls, data columns, and action groups to shared vertical and horizontal grid lines. Do not introduce page-specific spacing tokens unless a component absorbs a repeated host pattern.

### 5. Radius atoms

| Token | Size | Applies to |
|-------|------|------------|
| `--pvc-radius-control-sm` | 2px | Checkboxes, tight inputs |
| `--pvc-radius-control` | 4px | Text inputs, inline code focus shape |
| `--pvc-radius-action` | 6px | Buttons, tabs, grouped controls |
| `--pvc-radius-panel` | 8px | Data grids, grouped panels, preview frames |

Rules:

- Prefer sharper corners in dense clinical UI.
- Use `rounded-lg` (8px) only for larger grouped surfaces; it should match `--pvc-radius-panel`.
- Do not use `rounded-xl` or larger on standard product surfaces.
- Pills (`rounded-full`) are reserved for radios, switches, and avatars — not general panels.

### 6. Elevation atoms

| Level | Treatment |
|-------|-----------|
| Base | No shadow; border + surface contrast |
| Grouped | Muted surface step or strong border |
| Overlay | `--pvc-shadow-overlay` for tooltips, popovers, menus |

Do not use `shadow-lg` / `shadow-xl` in product examples.

### 7. Motion atoms

| Token | Duration | Use for |
|-------|----------|---------|
| `--pvc-duration-fast` | 120ms | Colour, border, background on controls |
| `--pvc-duration-default` | 160ms | General UI feedback |
| `--pvc-duration-overlay` | 200ms | Tooltip/popover appearance |

Transition colour, border, background, and opacity before movement. Respect `prefers-reduced-motion`.

## Surfaces

A **surface** is a bounded work region: panel, grid frame, fieldset, dialog body, or preview shell.

Standard surface recipe:

- Background: `--pvc-color-surface` or `--pvc-color-surface-muted`
- Border: 1px `--pvc-color-border`
- Radius: `--pvc-radius-panel` for large frames; `--pvc-radius-control` for inline fields
- No shadow unless the surface is an overlay

`Pathogen::DataGridComponent` is the primary framed surface in the library today. Host apps may compose equivalent panels from the same tokens until a shared `Pathogen::Panel` exists.

Typography **card preset** configures heading hierarchy for content inside a surface — it is not a bordered card component.

## Layout And Composition

- **Grid first** — columns, gutters, and dividers describe real structure.
- **Asymmetry with purpose** — offset primary and secondary work areas when workflow priority is genuinely uneven; never arbitrary decorative offset.
- **Density with breathing room** — compact layouts still leave room for focus rings, validation text, and row state.
- **Structure before ornament** — component anatomy (label → control → help → action) provides visual interest before icons or colour blocks.

References: restrained enterprise data tools (GitHub, dense Linear surfaces, public-sector utility UI) — not expressive marketing sites.

## Colour Application

- **Neutrals** own the environment: surfaces, borders, body text.
- **Accent** owns forward motion: primary actions, active navigation, meaningful links.
- **Status colours** own meaning: danger, warning, success, info — never atmosphere.
- **Strong colour blocks** stay small: selected row, active tab indicator, focus ring, status badge.

Do not use decorative gradients, violet/indigo feature blocks, or broad primary fills to make screens feel “designed.”

## Buttons

Buttons separate **meaning** (`tone`) from **hierarchy** (`emphasis`).

| Dimension | Values |
|-----------|--------|
| `tone` | `neutral`, `primary`, `danger` |
| `emphasis` | `outline`, `solid`, `ghost` |

Legacy `scheme` maps to presets: `default` → neutral outline, `primary` → primary solid, `danger` → danger outline.

See Button **Overview** and **Accessibility** previews for placement patterns.

### When To Use Each Combination

**Primary tone**

- `primary` + `solid` — single main forward action (Save, Submit, Continue).
- `primary` + `outline` — secondary brand action when a solid primary exists (Save draft, Apply filter).
- `primary` + `ghost` — tertiary brand-linked quiet action (View protocol, Open details).

**Neutral tone**

- `neutral` + `outline` — default secondary action (Cancel, Close).
- `neutral` + `ghost` — low-priority utility, toolbars, icon-only actions.
- `neutral` + `solid` — rare; strong neutral action when accent would mislead.

**Danger tone**

- `danger` + `outline` — destructive affordance with confirmation elsewhere.
- `danger` + `solid` — confirmed destructive step only (dialog confirm).
- `danger` + `ghost` — destructive utility in dense layouts.

### Placement And Hierarchy

- At most one `primary` + `solid` per action group.
- Form footers: main action last in reading order; cancel/back secondary.
- Do not place multiple `primary` + `solid` buttons side by side unless choices are genuinely equal.
- Toolbars: `small` size, `ghost` or `outline`, icon-only with accessible names.

### Size, Labels, And State

| Size | Use | Minimum target |
|------|-----|----------------|
| `medium` | Forms, dialogs, page actions | 44px |
| `small` | Toolbars, grids, dense tables | 24px |

- Labels: short verbs; no uppercase or wide tracking.
- Icon-only: `text`, `aria-label`, or `aria-labelledby`.
- `disabled` — not focusable. `aria_disabled` — focusable for validation feedback after activation.
- Link-styled buttons (`tag: :a`): same hover as `<button>`. Prefer `Pathogen::Link` for inline navigation.

## Links

`Pathogen::Link` is for inline text navigation within copy. It uses underline decoration and accent on hover. Button clusters use `Pathogen::Button`, not link styling.

## Form Controls

- Native controls first; custom controls preserve expected keyboard behaviour.
- Field labels: `text-sm font-semibold` with `--pvc-color-text`.
- Fieldsets: `gap-4` vertical rhythm.
- Checkboxes: `--pvc-radius-control-sm` / `rounded-sm`.
- Radios and switches: `rounded-full` tracks/knobs.
- Use `neutral-*` utilities only during migration; target `--pvc-color-*` for new work.
- Prefer `PathogenFormBuilder` and `Pathogen::Form::*` over ad hoc form markup.

## Data Grid

The data grid is a dense surface. It may use component-scoped tokens (`--pvc-data-grid-*`) and, in dark mode, a deeper body background (`neutral-950`) **inside the grid frame only** — not as the application canvas. See [Dark Mode](03-dark-mode).

States (hover, focus, selected, disabled) must remain visually distinct.

## Focus And Keyboard Access

Focus must be visible in light mode, dark mode, high-contrast, and forced-colours modes.

**Standard:** `focus-visible:outline-2 outline-[var(--pvc-color-focus)] outline-offset-2`

`Pathogen::Button` and `Pathogen::CopyableValue` implement this today. Link, Tabs, and Form controls may still use black/white outlines — acceptable for contrast, but **new and migrated code should converge on `--pvc-color-focus`** so host primary mapping applies consistently.

Rules:

- Do not use transparent borders to hide focus; forced-colours may expose them inconsistently.
- Custom controls must match native keyboard expectations.
- State must not rely on colour alone.

## Accessibility Baseline

Shared components must provide:

- Semantic HTML first.
- WCAG AA contrast for text and meaningful UI state.
- Visible keyboard focus.
- Screen-reader names, descriptions, and statuses matching visible UI.
- Reduced-motion handling for non-essential animation.
- Forced-colours / high-contrast support on custom controls.

## Deliberate Exceptions

Break the contract only when workflow genuinely requires it. Document:

- What broke the rule.
- Why the workflow needs it.
- Whether the pattern should become a shared component or token.

A healthy system evolves; it does not accumulate undocumented one-offs.
